<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    
      <p> In the diagram, the blocks are connected by an ideal string. The axle of the pulley and the inclined plane are frictionless; masses \(M_{1}\) and \(M_{2}\) as well as angle &#x3B8; are given. The system is held at rest and then released.
</p>
      <br/>
    
    <img width="474" alt="BK140" encrypturl="no" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK140.png"/>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11">
      <br/>
      
        <p>
Part 1. 
Which of the following statements are true?
</p>
      
      <part loncapaid="12">
        <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="no" loncapaid="24">
          <ul>
            <li>
              
                <p>Block \(M_{1}\) must be moving down the incline</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>Block \(M_{2}\) must be moving down the incline</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>There is just one specific ratio of \(M_{1}\) and \(M_{2}\) that may keep the blocks at rest</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>
There is a range of ratios of \(M_{1}\) and \(M_{2}\) that may keep the blocks at rest
</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil4" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>
Blocks \(M_{1}\) and \(M_{2}\) will have the same magnitude of acceleration
</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil5" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>
For block \(M_{1}\), the change in its kinetic energy is equal and opposite to the change in its potential energy
</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil6" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>
For block \(M_{2}\), the change in its kinetic energy is equal and opposite to the change in its potential energy
</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil7" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>
For the system of blocks \(M_{1}\) and \(M_{2}\), the change in its kinetic energy is equal and opposite to the change in its potential energy
</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil8" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>
The total momentum of blocks \(M_{1}\) and \(M_{2}\) remains constant
</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil9" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </optionresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="14">
        
