          </ul>
        </optionresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="16">
        
          <p>
Part 3. 
During the motion of the blocks, their speeds remain equal at all times as long as:
</p>
        
        <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="no" loncapaid="26">
          <ul>
            <li>
              
                <p>There is no friction in the system </p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>The connecting string has negligible mass</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
            </li>
            <li>
              
                <p>The connecting string does not stretch</p>
              
              <optioninput location="random" name="foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
